social_posts.post_text: This sport is brutiful, beautiful + brutal. (and yes a word i made up haha) I got to watch from the sidelines as the final event of qualification went down at Haleiwa. Falling off tour two years in a row, has given me the utmost deepest respect to all the athletes. While I wasn’t competing I could feel all the emotion that the Jersey carries. Every woman wearing it so well, there hearts on their sleeve, all embodying courage and resilience.  It’s crazy how a year all boils down to a moment filled with so much unknown and uncertainty and all you can do is trust. A huge congrats to all the women, the women who qualified and the women that showed so much grit and grace when everything was on the line. @sophie__mcculloch @bettylou.sakura.johnson @macyjanecallaghan @picklummolly @caitysimmers @alyssa_spencer1 @teresabonvalot @zoe_mcdougall @amurotsuzuki @kirrapink @sarahbaum___ @leilanimcgonagle @vahinefierro @sawyerlindblad @havannacabrero @kealatomoda @summermacedo @luanasilva__ @eweleiula @tessathyssen @briannacope @_indiarobinson @sophiamedina and so many more. ❤️

¡Con mucha alegría hoy anunciamos a @brisahennessy como nuestra primera Embajadora Nacional para UNICEF Costa Rica!

Brisa es un ejemplo de entrega y dedicación. Es una joven que está comprometida con la promoción de los derechos de todas las niñas, niños, adolescentes y jóvenes en Costa Rica.

Le damos la bienvenida a la familia UNICEF, en ocasión de la celebración de los 76 años de la fundación de nuestra organización, que lucha por los derechos #ParaCadaInfancia en todo el mundo.

@unicef @uniceflac

Vamos Brisa! 🙌 Earlier today,⁠ @unicef announced @brisahennessy as their first-ever National Ambassador in Costa Rica 💙⁠
⁠
As an Ambassador, Brisa will help raise awareness of children’s rights, such as lack of nutrition, girls’ empowerment, education, safe places to play and learn, climate change, poverty and the impact of sports to prevent violence.⁠

We are always excited to watch and support your journey in and out of the water, Brisa! 🙌⁠
⁠
“It’s an absolute honor to work with UNICEF. I have always been so passionate about bringing awareness to Children’s rights and to have that opportunity especially in my home of Costa Rica. I hope to make big changes together and provide a safe, happy and nurturing environment for future generations, because children are our future”, says Brisa.⁠

_

@unicef @unicef_costarica @ripcurl_costarica @ripcurl_usa⁠

Our brains - I had not truly grasped the extensive, incredible role it plays in being the controller and the source of life for every part of our being. I have had the privilege to work with Dr Keifer, Dr Creekmore, Dr Ferri and there incredible team at @brainhealthhawaii and I can’t emphasize enough the difference I have felt in my everyday life - physically and mentally. To have the ability to experience, learn, feel and witness first hand the incredible changes and understand the complexity of something I take for granted everyday. Before going into there clinic I had a very complicated diagnosis, no clear path and to be honest not feeling my best. I’ve had over 25 treatments and while I still have a lot more work to do I feel confident in my healing journey thanks to my brain health Ohana. Whatever your going through, whether that be mentally or physically - brain health, sleep & mental health is something we need to prioritize more. Thank you @rissmoore10 for connecting us.❤️

Every time I lose or am overwhelmed by uncertainty I find myself trying to quickly move on, run from the noise, rush to the next thing, but it’s in those moments that I constantly have to remind myself that the only thing that is certain is the moments right now and appreciating them. Lots of tears, laughter and goosebumps this event. From watching the incredible performances - the winners, the stories. To watching @owright surf his last event - celebrating the inspirational human and athlete he is. We sat with Owen before the event started and he gave us some wisdom that will last with me forever. Through adversity and challenge the way to find peace, to find flow, to bring out your “best self” is not by complicating  or adding more but stripping down the layers  to find who you are in your being, who you are in your core. It all begins and ends with the mind/heart and we all have that ability to choose. 🤍

Los desafíos y las dificultades son una forma que te hace dar un paso atrás y apreciar todos los pequeños momentos.  Muchas lágrimas, risas y lecciones este evento.  Encontrar más paz y motivación para el próximo.🙏

Poetry has always been my therapy and how I express my feelings. Vulnerability has been my word for this year and so i take this step. If I have learned one thing about this fast pace life and healing journey is the underestimated word of compassion. No matter what someone’s life looks like on the outside , everyone’s fighting a battle we know nothing about, I feel that and I see that so much more now. While there are many good days I feel like I’m constantly in a battle with my mind and my body and I sometimes I want to give up. In the ideal world I wanted to share my story once I was “better” the truth is I know the journey is going to be long and if I could help someone not feel alone right now why wouldn’t l. Since I was 16 years old I suffered with body image, dysmorphia and had an eating disorder that lasted almost 3 years, in the process I lost my cycle for over 2 years and it led me down a pretty toxic path. Last year I got diagnosed with hypothyroidism, depression, EBV, and just recently a pituatary gland adenoma. I have suffered from brain fog, insanely low energy, have gained over 20 pounds in a matter of 6 months and have watched my body change before my eyes. Being a woman and an athlete I struggle with this deeply everyday. But while im the biggest my body has ever been, I see my body now, i have a deeper awareness and appreciation of my body that i thought I would never known. Thyroid and hormone complications is one of the most common diseases in women and is growing more rapidly with the more toxins, and the trend of eating disorders in this world. While it’s been the hardest time of my life I have gained more self love and perspective than I never would have reached if I didn’t go through this. If I could offer any advice: Understand your cycles, the importance of how you cope with stress, practice more self love, being more gentle even in the hardest of times and to surround yourself with the right support crew. You are are not alone. If anyone is going through similar things please feel free to reach out. sending all my love.❤️

How do your stats stack up against @brisahennessy? ⁠
⁠
We tracked every surf and analysed your data from your Rip Curl SearchGPS watch and scored you in real-time. The scoring criteria was based on 2 key metrics: wave length and wave speed. Bonus points were allocated for surfing a new location and wave density.⁠
⁠
Brisa’s wave length of 663ft and wave speed of 19.23mp/h, across 3 locations gave her a score of 4952. ⁠
⁠
How to enter:⁠
1. Check your inbox to find your personalised Virtual Pro entry video (you need be an existing SearchGPS user who has logged surfs over the 10-day period March 2023 to be eligible).⁠
2. Share your personalised video on Instagram as a Reel, adding the hashtag #RipCurlVirtualPro to the caption - this will automatically enter you into the contest.⁠
3. Ensure your Instagram account is set to public so we can confirm your entry!⁠
⁠
The winner will be announced June 5th, 2023.⁠

“The wound is the place where the light enters you.” - Rumi
Hey everyone I wanted to share where I am at.
I haven’t surfed in a month and my life has slowed down immensely. Sometimes it’s the lack of noise - to truly sit in the silience of being that scares me the most. To face uncertainty everyday and to lose control of things that once was. I have been immersed in the in between moments of life and that has given me a whole new perspective of living and being. Healing has made me face uncomfortable truths, my deepest fears, but it has made me realize that it creates a path you would have never walked on to find who you needed to become. 
Sometimes you need to hike into the forest and hug a tree, yell off a Cliff to find your voice, hit rock bottom to see all that lays in front of you. How do you heal? 
Feeling all the love and sending all of my love back. 🤍

“La herida es el lugar por donde entra la luz.” - Rumi
Hola a todos, quería compartir dónde estoy.

No he surfeado en un mes y mi vida ha bajado sus revoluciones inmensamente. A veces, lo que más me asusta es la falta de ruido, sentarme verdaderamente en el silencio del ser.  Enfrentar la incertidumbre todos los días y perder el control de las cosas que alguna vez fueron.  He estado inmersa en los momentos intermedios de la vida y eso me ha dado una perspectiva completamente nueva de la vida.  La sanación me ha hecho enfrentar verdades incómodas, mis miedos más profundos, pero a la vez,  me ha hecho darme cuenta de que crea un camino que nunca hubieras recorrido para encontrar en quién necesitabas convertirte.
 
A veces necesitas caminar por el bosque para abrazar un árbol, gritar desde un acantilado para encontrar tu voz, tocar fondo para ver todo lo que hay frente a ti. 

¿Cómo te curas?
 Sintiendo todo el amor y enviando todo mi amor de vuelta.🤍

Mi corazón. 🩵 Agradecida de haber pasado estos días con mi @unicefcostarica familia. Tuve el placer de visitar 'Espacios Seguros' en Quepos y lo único que puedo decir es que los niños son luz y solo pueden brillar cuando les damos nuestra mano, nuestro amor y nuestro apoyo. No importa su situación o condición en casa, cada uno de ellos se presentó con sonrisas, corazones y mentes abiertas para aprender y para compartir. Ellos son el ejemplo. Gracias @unicefcostarica ​​por crear este espacio tan seguro para que ellos y ellas puedan ser realmente vistos y apoyados. 

En Costa Rica 4 de cada 10 niños viven en pobreza y las cifras van en aumento.  Sigamos trabajando juntos para que ellos tengan la oportunidad de una vida mejor.

So grateful to have had the opportunity of visiting “Espacios seguros” with @unicef and spend some time with the most amazing children and volunteers. All I can say is kids are the light and they can only shine when we give them our hand, our love and support. No matter their situation or their condition at home, Each of them showed up with smiles, open hearts, open minds, to learn, to share and to give. Thank you @unicefcostarica for creating this safe space so they can be truly seen and  supported. 
4 out of 10 children in Costa Rica deal with poverty and the numbers are increasing. Let’s continue to work together so that they have opportunity’s for a better life. 

Muchas gracias por todo el apoyo @bluehorizoncosta @hotelespadillagardens y a todos los que lo hicieron posible🙏🫶🏼

“The truth of our mortality awakens us to life most profoundly.” This month and everday I honor all the warriors and my warrior mama.💗 @puravida x @b4bc 
 In 2012 my mama was diagnosed with breast cancer and we went through the hardest most transformative time of our lives. It’s not just how you beat cancer with your strength but how you beat it with love. You never let me feel scared because you met everyday with pure presence and endless light & positivity for “this moment.” Thank you for continually showing me that in the deepest of challenges & adversity - strength, kindness, gratitude, love always wins.  I remember taking you surfing everyday, no matter rain or shine, times when it was even a struggle to get in the ocean. But everyday I swear a little part of you healed. Mother Nature heals, connections heal, love heals. I love you mom. To everyone going through or have been through, sending all my love.🩷🩷🩷 @hennymama
#breastcancerawarenessmonth

Come make Dads and I’s favorite ceviche recipe with us!  A Fijian fusion twist on a Costa Rican ceviche! Trying to live more sustainably out here in the jungle. Dad caught the fish, limes & herbs from our garden, and coconuts from our neighbor. Buen provecho and Da Kana! 🇨🇷🇫🇯🫶🏼Recipe below. :)

•5 cups of fresh fish of your choice. Coconut meat or palm heart for vegan option)
•The juice of 10 limes.
•1 cup Coconut cream ( can be fresh or canned.)
•1 red onion finely chopped
•1 red bell pepper finely chopped
•1 tablespoon of finely minced ginger 
•1 large bunch of cilantro finely chopped
Optional: 1 jalapeño finely chopped
Optional: 1/2 cup young coconut meat 
•Salt and pepper to taste.
( Makes around 5 servings.) 

Dice the fish into small cubes and add into a large bowl. Add in the lime juice and the rest of the chopped herbs and vegetables. Add salt and pepper to taste. 

¡Ven a preparar nuestra receta de ceviche favorita con nosotros! Un toque fiyiano en un ceviche costarricense :)Tratando de vivir de manera más sostenible aquí en la jungla, mi papá pescó unos buenos, trajo limón y hierbas de nuestro jardín y cocos de nuestro vecino.

5 tazas de pescado fresco de tu elección. Coco o palmito (para opción vegana)
El jugo de 10 limones.
1 taza de crema de coco (puede ser natural o enlatada).
1 cebolla morada finamente picada
1 chile dulce finamente picado
1 cucharada de jengibre finamente picado
1 rollo grande de culantro finamente picado
Opcional: 1 chile jalapeño finamente picado
Opcional: 1/2 taza de pulpa de coco tierno
Sal y pimienta al gusto. 
(Rinde 5 para porciones).

Corta el pescado en cubos pequeños y colócalo en un bowl grande. Agrega el jugo de limón y el resto de las hierbas y verduras picadas. Añadir sal y pimienta al gusto. Buen provecho!

January is thyroid awareness month.🦋Still navigating my way through my own journey with this. But to everyone who is going through it you are not alone! 
It’s been a frustrating process going through the trials and tribulations, the ebbs and flows of what works for my body but also it’s been the most gratifying - Because for the first time I’m listening and not fighting. 
I’m realizing more and more it’s a marathon not a sprint when it comes to healing, what you don’t water everyday won’t grow. So be patient, be kind and gentle with the process and tend to the inner garden so it can grow. Every body is different so what works for me might not work for you but here are some things I’ve been focusing on. 
- Regulating my cortisol levels 
- Prioritizing sleep
- Understanding my cycles
- Eliminating toxins 
- Daily detox 
- Reducing stress 
-Eating a balanced whole food diet 
- Getting enough Iron + protein
- Grounding & grattitude 
- Positive self talk 

Will go more in depth in these on part 2 of this series.
